  <text name="characterHelp" >
    <page>
      <p>[Unit Screen]</p>
      <p>Use this screen to pick up and drop items, wear armor, and select a weapon. You can also view statistics
         about the current unit.</p>
      <p>The name of the weapon the unit is holding is displayed in the top left. Beside the name is the tech level, from 1 to 3.
         Higher tech levels indicate better weapons and armor.</p>
    </page>
    <page image="helpImage4">
      <p>[Inventory]</p>
      <p>
        What the unit is carrying. The top row is in use: the currently worn armor and currently carried
        weapon. You can tap to drop an item, or drag to organize items.</p>
      <p>
        For weapons, the total rounds available for that weapon is displayed below the name.
      </p>
    </page>

    <page image="helpImage5">
      <p>[Items on the Ground]</p>
      <p>
       The row of tabs select Terran Weapons, Alien Weapons, Armor/Shields,
       and Miscellaneous items. Tap to select a group to view. Tap an item to pick it up.
      </p>
      <p>
        The number of items available is displayed beneath the item name.
      </p>
    </page>

    <page>
      <p>[Stats and Numbers]</p>
      <p> The lower right buttons show unit traits, abilitites, and statistics.</p>
      <p> 'Inv' is the default inventory screen. 'Stats' shows the unit statistics. 'Wpns' compares weapons carried and on the ground, 
          with buttons to select range.</p>
    </page>
  </text>

